node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parks Project in Yellowstone National Park with @parksproject, @yellowstonenps, and @luisramirezphotos. May be an image of body of water and nature.

node.text:
This water may look inviting, but the geothermal pools of @yellowstonenps can reach temperatures of up to 456°F (237°C)! Which water feature is your favorite in Yellowstone?

Photo by @luisramirezphotos
📍Photo taken on Crow, Eastern Shoshone, and Cheyenne native lands. #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter 

Notice: While we continue to share photos and stories from the wild lands we love, keep in mind, every park has different opening dates and restrictions. Be sure you are following all local, state, and federal guidelines.

node.text:
Explore Acadia, Grand Canyon, Joshua Tree, Rocky Mountain, and Yosemite with a bird's-eye view 🦅  Our collection with @hankskerchiefs explores the wonder of national parks in a series of limited edition handkerchiefs inspired by the flora, fauna, and landscapes. #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

Every purchase from the collection supports the National Parks Conservation Association (@npcapics) in the efforts to preserve our public lands for future generations.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parks Project in Glacier National Park with @parksproject, @glaciernps, and @cactus.queen.studios. May be an image of lake, nature and mountain.

node.text:
With water this clear, it's no wonder the hike to Avalanche Lake is one of the most popular hikes in @Glaciernps! This 5.9-mile out and back trek is not far from the West Entrance of the park near Lake McDonald. Remember to practice safe hiking and Leave No Trace principles when visiting. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

Photo by @cactus.queen.studios
📍Photo taken on Blackfoot and Ktunaxa ɂamakɂis native lands.

Notice: While we continue to share photos and stories from the wild lands we love, keep in mind, every park has different opening dates and restrictions. Be sure you are following all local, state, and federal guidelines.

There's something ✨ magical ✨ about @yosemitenps. Planning a summer visit? Millions of people visit Yosemite from April to October. While Yosemite Valley is the main destination for most visitors, there are many places explore! Need some help planning? Check out our Park Finder for a complete list of activities! #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

Photo by @shanewarephoto
📍Photo taken on Northern Paiute, Western Mono/Monache, Central Sierra Miwok, and Southern Sierra Miwok native lands.

node.text:
Our first national park, @Yellowstonenps, is home to more than half of the world’s geothermal features and 75 percent of the world’s geysers! The park has an estimated 1283 geysers spread across nine geyser basins, so there's plenty to see on your visit. #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

Photo by @luisramirezphotos
📍Photo taken on Crow, Eastern Shoshone, and Cheyenne native lands.

node.text:
We get it, it's tough picking out the right gear for the trail or crag. Our newest collection with @Gramicci is all about getting out there in style with quality pants and tees that get the job done, whether it's at the crag or on your next hike. 🧗 We want to be sure everyone has the opportunity to explore the way they want, which is why every purchase gives back to @accessfund, a nonprofit dedicated to protecting America's climbing. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark 

Photos by @urbanclimbr 📸
